Good point.
@rjrudin, @brucean52, what do you think about this?
  const sendAndHandle = (requestFunction, errorFunction) => {
    try {
      requestFunction();
    } catch (error) {
      if (error.response.status === 400) {
        if (error.response.data.hasOwnProperty('message')) {
          errorFunction(error['response']['data']['message']);
        }
      } else {
        handleError(error);
      }
    } finally {
      resetSessionTime();
    }
  };

We can then use the requestFunction to make the request, open/close modal, etc. Similary we can also use errorFunction to set error message, open/close modal, etc.

