After a couple of discussions, @brucean52  and I came down with the following function:
function sendAndHandle(requestFunction, errorFunction, resetSessionTime) {
  try {
    requestFunction();
  } catch (error) {
    errorFunction(error);
  } finally {
    resetSessionTime();
  }
}
export default sendAndHandle;

The entire catch block is replaced with errorFunction(error); in order to support more customization and we need to pass in the resetSessionTime function since useContext hook for resetSessionTime only works in react components and this isn't one.
At this point, this just seems to be a try/catch handler and it doesn't seem worth adding it to a common library.

